ui: require CTRL+C confirmation to quit and remove unused VAULT_DOCKER_NETWORK
- Replace 'q' key quit binding with CTRL+C requiring double-press confirmation
- Add quit confirmation dialog visible across all views (dashboard, logs, config, wizard, action)
- Implement quitConfirm state management with automatic cancellation on any non-CTRL+C keypress
- Remove VAULT_DOCKER_NETWORK from wizard prompts and validators (unused configuration variable)
- Update all footer hints and help messages to display CTRL+C instead of 'q' for quitting
- Reset quit confirmation state on view transitions to prevent lingering prompts

This change prevents accidental application exit when typing 'q' in the wizard
input fields and provides a safety mechanism requiring explicit confirmation
before quitting.

fix: resolve naming inconsistencies and standardize environment loading
- Standardize VAULT_* variables in Go CLI (PLUGIN→SERVICE, REPLICAS→WEB_REPLICAS, etc.)
- Align VAULT_ROTATION_INTERVAL to 120s
- Fix wizard time unit (minutes→seconds)
- Standardize LOG_LEVEL → DOCKER_PROXY_LOG_LEVEL
- Rename orchestrator/SECURITY.md → SECURITY_RUNTIME.md
- Add load_env_with_override() and refactor environment loading
- Improve Python guidelines compliance (imports, annotations)
- Clean up debug logs and improve documentation

Fixes 15 issues identified during technical audit.

