chore(release): prepare v1.1.0 changelog and cleanup

feat(tui): implement view navigation, interactive wizard, and config management
- Add ViewState-based navigation with clean transitions and auto-return to dashboard.
- Integrate interactive wizard with dynamic field loading and template initialization.
- Add Config view with categorized variables, scrolling, and password toggle.

feat: Add Bubbletea-based leyzenctl TUI dashboard with live controls
- Added a Bubbletea and Lipgloss-powered leyzenctl dashboard featuring status polling, live log view, and keyboard-driven lifecycle actions for restart, start, stop, and rebuild.
- Made the TUI the default root command with a --no-ui flag for headless mode.
- Updated compose helpers to stream output to the interface and documented the new interactive workflow in the changelog.

feat(env): propagate "--env-file" override into compose manifest generation
The build system now updates all env_file entries with the selected environment file.
Ensures Docker Compose reflects the correct variables during builds.
Adds clear logging when a custom environment file is applied.

fix: Improve Filebrowser entrypoint privilege handling and startup resilience
- Relaxed privilege dropping to allow container startup when mounted volumes are unwritable, easing recovery on restrictive hosts.
- Fixed a regression causing `tmp: parameter not set` errors during write-access checks.
- Handled pre-existing databases gracefully so restarts no longer loop when only the settings file is missing.

docs: migrate documentation to dedicated GitHub Wiki
- Removed local technical and maintainer guides now centralized in the official wiki.
- Updated README and SECURITY references to point toward the new documentation.
- Cleaned obsolete developer and operations files from /docs and root.
- Added changelog and contributor notes reflecting the wiki migration.

Added read-only permission to the CI workflow

feat: Replace service.sh with Cobra-based leyzenctl CLI and update docs
- Introduced a full-featured leyzenctl CLI built with Cobra, including start, stop, restart, build, status, and configuration subcommands.
- Added supporting modules for Docker control, environment handling, and validation.
- Removed service.sh and updated all guides, templates, and policies to reference the new CLI.
- Created LEYZENCTL.md and refreshed README, CONTRIBUTING, and CHANGELOG accordingly.

fix: Dynamically import orchestrator configuration for CI and container compatibility
- Modified the entrypoint to dynamically import the orchestrator configuration module after resolving the package path, ensuring it runs correctly in both CI and container environments.
- Preserved defensive error handling and static-analysis hints for ConfigurationError.

